description: Located in the vibrant Morningside Heights neighborhood, just a short walk from Columbia University, this beautiful, spacious 2-bedroom, 1-bathroom apartment is a true gem. The apartment is filled with natural light, enhancing its warm ambiance and  making it the perfect place for you to settle down and call home.This charming residence at 605 West 11th Street is housed within a beautifully preserved co-op building, originally constructed in 1905 and showcasing the elegant Beaux-Arts architectural style. The Markenfield, as the building is known, rises gracefully over  six stories and is home to fifty-two units. Its rich history and meticulously maintained fa ade radiates a sense of timeless charm.With the amenities, you'll find the convenience of a resident superintendent dedicated to ensuring the upkeep of the building. The area boasts many cafes, restaurants, entertainment venues, open-air markets, and specialty shops.Convenient subway stations, such as the #1 at 110th and Broadway, the B and C lines at 110th and Central Park West, and the crosstown bus at 110th and Broadway, make this location ideal for reaching all areas of the city.Please, no pets of any kind.
